bad case of pneumonia.

00:39:50.100 --> 00:39:52.490 align:middle line:84%
About 24 hours later,
I was in the hospital

00:39:52.490 --> 00:39:56.750 align:middle line:84%
on intravenous antibiotics for
swollen meninges of the brain,

00:39:56.750 --> 00:40:00.800 align:middle line:84%
septicemia, multiple
organ failures,

00:40:00.800 --> 00:40:02.660 align:middle line:90%
and severe chronic disease.

00:40:02.660 --> 00:40:06.510 align:middle line:84%
My chances of survival
were actually only 40%.

00:40:06.510 --> 00:40:07.550 align:middle line:90%
Something changed.

00:40:07.550 --> 00:40:09.920 align:middle line:84%
And it was probably a
combination of everything

00:40:09.920 --> 00:40:13.120 align:middle line:84%
that went on, but I remember
leaving the hospital.

00:40:13.120 --> 00:40:15.470 align:middle line:90%
And I wasn't the same person.

00:40:15.470 --> 00:40:18.440 align:middle line:84%
Any like happiness
for life was gone.

00:40:18.440 --> 00:40:21.090 align:middle line:84%
I was very apathetic
and depressed.

00:40:21.090 --> 00:40:24.260 align:middle line:84%
I seemed to be really
struggling to believe

00:40:24.260 --> 00:40:27.800 align:middle line:84%
in a positive future for
myself and self-conscious

00:40:27.800 --> 00:40:29.600 align:middle line:90%
and a lot more introverted.

00:40:29.600 --> 00:40:32.480 align:middle line:84%
All of this sort of
made me focus on--

00:40:32.480 --> 00:40:35.180 align:middle line:84%
made me begin focusing
on what I felt

00:40:35.180 --> 00:40:37.700 align:middle line:84%
I could control,
which is what I ate,

00:40:37.700 --> 00:40:40.400 align:middle line:84%
how I looked, how
other people saw me.

00:40:40.400 --> 00:40:44.480 align:middle line:84%
And I think I used
obsession with my body

00:40:44.480 --> 00:40:47.930 align:middle line:84%
and controlling
my intake as a way

00:40:47.930 --> 00:40:51.980 align:middle line:84%
to be accepted, feel
connected to the world

00:40:51.980 --> 00:40:55.070 align:middle line:84%
and the environment to
be a part of something,

00:40:55.070 --> 00:40:56.820 align:middle line:90%
to feel home somewhere.

00:40:56.820 --> 00:41:02.150 align:middle line:90%


00:41:02.150 --> 00:41:06.620 align:middle line:84%
I remember looking in the
mirror and hating my body

00:41:06.620 --> 00:41:08.270 align:middle line:90%
and judging it so harshly.

00:41:08.270 --> 00:41:11.060 align:middle line:84%
So I had a lot of different
health conditions.

00:41:11.060 --> 00:41:20.520 align:middle line:90%


00:41:20.520 --> 00:41:23.880 align:middle line:84%
My main conditions I was
dealing with autoimmune thyroid

00:41:23.880 --> 00:41:27.840 align:middle line:84%
disease, extreme hypothyroid,
and thyroid goiter.

00:41:27.840 --> 00:41:31.680 align:middle line:84%
So it's actually very difficult
to swallow and eat food.

00:41:31.680 --> 00:41:35.520 align:middle line:84%
I had a gastroparesis, so
really slow stomach emptying

00:41:35.520 --> 00:41:39.060 align:middle line:84%
and chronic stomach inflammation
and gastritis, probably

00:41:39.060 --> 00:41:41.610 align:middle line:84%
from years of an eating
disorder and antibiotics

00:41:41.610 --> 00:41:43.170 align:middle line:90%
and all that stuff as well.

00:41:43.170 --> 00:41:45.480 align:middle line:84%
I had really bad
irritable bowel syndrome

00:41:45.480 --> 00:41:48.520 align:middle line:84%
and chronic inflammatory
bowel disease.

00:41:48.520 --> 00:41:52.260 align:middle line:84%
So I was bloated all the time,
a lot of pain in the bathroom,

00:41:52.260 --> 00:41:54.390 align:middle line:90%
more than anybody should be.

00:41:54.390 --> 00:41:56.910 align:middle line:84%
And my most painful
condition by far

00:41:56.910 --> 00:42:00.510 align:middle line:84%
and what actually prompted me to
start my YouTube channel, what

00:42:00.510 --> 00:42:02.520 align:middle line:84%
I really focused
on at the beginning

00:42:02.520 --> 00:42:05.610 align:middle line:84%
was one of the top three most
painful conditions that exist.

00:42:05.610 --> 00:42:08.040 align:middle line:84%
And it was
interstitial cystitis.

00:42:08.040 --> 00:42:12.090 align:middle line:84%
So it's a chronic
ulcerative bladder disease.

00:42:12.090 --> 00:42:15.810 align:middle line:84%
The symptoms are a lot
of urgency, burning pain,

00:42:15.810 --> 00:42:17.220 align:middle line:90%
but you have no life.

00:42:17.220 --> 00:42:19.780 align:middle line:84%
You're kind of housebound
and living in your bathroom

00:42:19.780 --> 00:42:20.580 align:middle line:90%
in a lot of pain.

00:42:20.580 --> 00:42:22.650 align:middle line:84%
This is where I
lived for two years.

00:42:22.650 --> 00:42:26.010 align:middle line:84%
I was a prisoner
in my own bathroom.

00:42:26.010 --> 00:42:30.930 align:middle line:84%
And I had my identity stripped
by my eating disorder.

00:42:30.930 --> 00:42:32.650 align:middle line:84%
I really didn't
have a life at all.

00:42:32.650 --> 00:42:34.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Anorexics fast all the time.

00:42:34.080 --> 00:42:36.680 align:middle line:84%
I mean, some people may
justify fasting if they

00:42:36.680 --> 00:42:37.680 align:middle line:90%
have an eating disorder.

00:42:37.680 --> 00:42:39.090 align:middle line:84%
They may say,
well, look, fasting

00:42:39.090 --> 00:42:41.070 align:middle line:84%
is fixing all these
other medical problems.

00:42:41.070 --> 00:42:43.862 align:middle line:84%
We know that eating disorders
are medical and biological.

00:42:43.862 --> 00:42:45.570 align:middle line:84%
We're talking about
brain-based disorder.

00:42:45.570 --> 00:42:47.940 align:middle line:84%
Maybe fasting will fix
my eating disorder.

00:42:47.940 --> 00:42:50.530 align:middle line:84%
Well, anorexics
fast all the time.

00:42:50.530 --> 00:42:52.040 align:middle line:90%
It makes their disorder worst.

00:42:52.040 --> 00:42:54.727 align:middle line:84%
Bulimics purge food
in a number of ways.

00:42:54.727 --> 00:42:57.060 align:middle line:84%
Self-induced vomiting is the
one that people think about

00:42:57.060 --> 00:42:59.477 align:middle line:84%
or misuse of laxatives, which
actually does nothing to get

00:42:59.477 --> 00:43:00.750 align:middle line:90%
rid of calories, by the way.

00:43:00.750 --> 00:43:04.290 align:middle line:84%
But the other thing that
bulimic do to purge is fast.

00:43:04.290 --> 00:43:06.690 align:middle line:84%
So both bulimics
and anorexics fast.

00:43:06.690 --> 00:43:08.160 align:middle line:84%
And it makes their
disorder worse.

00:43:08.160 --> 00:43:09.460 align:middle line:90%
It does not fix it.

00:43:09.460 --> 00:43:12.980 align:middle line:84%
>> We did see that in the
archaeological record.

00:43:12.980 --> 00:43:16.290 align:middle line:84%
Bulimics-- in a
member in Rome, they

00:43:16.290 --> 00:43:20.280 align:middle line:84%
had the vomitoria where they
would eat and gorge themselves.

00:43:20.280 --> 00:43:21.990 align:middle line:90%
And then they'd go throw up.

00:43:21.990 --> 00:43:24.900 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that the Romans and
the vomitoriums that they would

00:43:24.900 --> 00:43:26.910 align:middle line:84%
have was sort of a
different phenomenon.

00:43:26.910 --> 00:43:31.560 align:middle line:84%
That was much more
of a social activity,

00:43:31.560 --> 00:43:34.583 align:middle line:84%
where people would go and
overindulge on purpose.

00:43:34.583 --> 00:43:36.000 align:middle line:84%
And then they would
vomit in order

00:43:36.000 --> 00:43:39.180 align:middle line:84%
to continue to be
able to do that.

00:43:39.180 --> 00:43:41.910 align:middle line:84%
Patients with bulimia, where
they will binge and then

00:43:41.910 --> 00:43:44.940 align:middle line:84%
purge often by
vomiting, they find

00:43:44.940 --> 00:43:48.600 align:middle line:84%
that both the binging and the
purging to be highly shameful.

00:43:48.600 --> 00:43:50.700 align:middle line:84%
They will go to great
lengths to hide this

00:43:50.700 --> 00:43:52.080 align:middle line:84%
from their friends,
their family.

00:43:52.080 --> 00:43:54.840 align:middle line:84%
It's not something they
feel comfortable doing,

00:43:54.840 --> 00:43:58.060 align:middle line:90%
in generally, in public.

00:43:58.060 --> 00:44:02.890 align:middle line:84%
>> I remember the first
time I actually purged.

00:44:02.890 --> 00:44:05.920 align:middle line:90%
And it wasn't with intent.

00:44:05.920 --> 00:44:08.540 align:middle line:84%
I literally had
eaten what I thought

00:44:08.540 --> 00:44:10.600 align:middle line:84%
I shouldn't after a
long time of anorexia,

00:44:10.600 --> 00:44:12.730 align:middle line:84%
after many months of
really starving myself

00:44:12.730 --> 00:44:14.650 align:middle line:90%
to the point of insanity.

00:44:14.650 --> 00:44:17.260 align:middle line:90%
And I remember I was so hungry.

00:44:17.260 --> 00:44:18.430 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't-- I gave in.

00:44:18.430 --> 00:44:20.950 align:middle line:84%
It was like a
physiological survival

00:44:20.950 --> 00:44:23.220 align:middle line:90%
urge I couldn't ignore.

00:44:23.220 --> 00:44:26.710 align:middle line:84%
And I was so anxious
while I was eating that I

00:44:26.710 --> 00:44:28.600 align:middle line:90%
felt such an upset stomach.

00:44:28.600 --> 00:44:32.080 align:middle line:84%
It felt like I was doing
something so wrong.

00:44:32.080 --> 00:44:36.820 align:middle line:84%
And afterwards-- I mean, I
ate until I couldn't breathe.

00:44:36.820 --> 00:44:38.560 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't control myself.

00:44:38.560 --> 00:44:41.020 align:middle line:84%
It was just-- I was
like my body needed it.

00:44:41.020 --> 00:44:46.360 align:middle line:84%
And then I felt so
worried and panicky that I

00:44:46.360 --> 00:44:48.400 align:middle line:84%
was going to gain
a ton of weight,

00:44:48.400 --> 00:44:50.320 align:middle line:84%
destroy everything
I had already done.

00:44:50.320 --> 00:44:53.540 align:middle line:84%
I came in the bathroom
really frantic and scared.

00:44:53.540 --> 00:44:55.510 align:middle line:84%
And I sort of leaned
over the toilet bowl.

00:44:55.510 --> 00:44:58.810 align:middle line:84%
And I was so painfully
full that just the act

00:44:58.810 --> 00:45:02.680 align:middle line:84%
of leaning over, I mean, food
practically came up itself.

00:45:02.680 --> 00:45:04.300 align:middle line:90%
And it was so painful coming up.

00:45:04.300 --> 00:45:07.480 align:middle line:84%
It was like fire or lava
just shooting out of you.

00:45:07.480 --> 00:45:11.890 align:middle line:84%
And at the same time, I was
flooded with a sense of relief.

00:45:11.890 --> 00:45:14.080 align:middle line:84%
It was like I could get
rid of all the shame.

00:45:14.080 --> 00:45:16.270 align:middle line:84%
I could get rid of all
the pain in my life.

00:45:16.270 --> 00:45:19.520 align:middle line:84%
I could just be back to
the way I was before.

00:45:19.520 --> 00:45:21.580 align:middle line:84%
And then I would feel
really panicky and shaky.

00:45:21.580 --> 00:45:23.200 align:middle line:84%
And I would wonder
if anybody hurt me.

00:45:23.200 --> 00:45:25.870 align:middle line:84%
And I would be afraid
that I smelled like vomit.

00:45:25.870 --> 00:45:28.400 align:middle line:84%
And I just felt really
dirty and really disgusting.

00:45:28.400 --> 00:45:30.650 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted to pretend the
whole thing didn't happen.

00:45:30.650 --> 00:45:34.870 align:middle line:84%
So I would rush over to the sink
and just put so much toothpaste

00:45:34.870 --> 00:45:35.770 align:middle line:90%
on my toothbrush.

00:45:35.770 --> 00:45:38.410 align:middle line:84%
And I was so afraid I
had like splatter on me.

00:45:38.410 --> 00:45:42.870 align:middle line:84%
I just felt so disgusting, I
guess, on such a deep level

00:45:42.870 --> 00:45:46.300 align:middle line:84%
that I would sit-in the
bath for a long time.

00:45:46.300 --> 00:45:48.670 align:middle line:84%
And I would just run the
hot water over my hands

00:45:48.670 --> 00:45:52.810 align:middle line:84%
and splash my face and just feel
really ashamed and embarrassed

00:45:52.810 --> 00:45:55.660 align:middle line:84%
and hope that nobody ever
knew that I did this,

00:45:55.660 --> 00:45:58.330 align:middle line:84%
because it felt like the most
despicable thing on planet

00:45:58.330 --> 00:45:59.410 align:middle line:90%
Earth.

00:45:59.410 --> 00:46:01.270 align:middle line:84%
>> When the recovery
battle began,

00:46:01.270 --> 00:46:05.440 align:middle line:90%
I was 145 pounds and 6 foot 3.

00:46:05.440 --> 00:46:09.430 align:middle line:84%
And now I stand
today at 188 pounds.

00:46:09.430 --> 00:46:12.880 align:middle line:84%
I just had maybe a inferiority
complex, if you will.

00:46:12.880 --> 00:46:14.572 align:middle line:84%
I was bullied as a
little as a young kid

00:46:14.572 --> 00:46:16.030 align:middle line:84%
and growing up
through high school.

00:46:16.030 --> 00:46:16.930 align:middle line:90%
And it always made me angry.

00:46:16.930 --> 00:46:17.770 align:middle line:90%
And it made me mad.

00:46:17.770 --> 00:46:20.408 align:middle line:84%
And it felt like, if I
could work out harder,

00:46:20.408 --> 00:46:22.450 align:middle line:84%
and if I could watch my
diet even tighter, that's

00:46:22.450 --> 00:46:25.210 align:middle line:90%
a way to get back at everybody.

00:46:25.210 --> 00:46:29.610 align:middle line:84%
And it caused me to have
very bad social anxiety.

00:46:29.610 --> 00:46:32.410 align:middle line:84%
It just led me to a
life of isolation,

00:46:32.410 --> 00:46:34.570 align:middle line:84%
because I was afraid
that I was going

00:46:34.570 --> 00:46:36.240 align:middle line:84%
to eat something
that was unhealthy,

00:46:36.240 --> 00:46:39.300 align:middle line:84%
or I was afraid that I was going
to smell something and want

00:46:39.300 --> 00:46:40.505 align:middle line:90%
it and not have it.

00:46:40.505 --> 00:46:41.880 align:middle line:84%
And I would feel
massive anxiety.

00:46:41.880 --> 00:46:44.920 align:middle line:84%
So I would just talk myself out
of not going to these places.

00:46:44.920 --> 00:46:47.550 align:middle line:84%
So I came home for
Thanksgiving one year.

00:46:47.550 --> 00:46:49.540 align:middle line:84%
And my brother
handed me this packet

00:46:49.540 --> 00:46:51.100 align:middle line:90%
that said orthorexia on it.

00:46:51.100 --> 00:46:53.368 align:middle line:84%
And he threw it at me and
he said you have this.

00:46:53.368 --> 00:46:54.168 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:46:54.168 --> 00:47:15.000 align:middle line:90%
>> (SINGING)

00:47:15.000 --> 00:47:18.830 align:middle line:84%
Orthorexia is a condition where
you take things to the extreme.

00:47:18.830 --> 00:47:21.890 align:middle line:84%
I specifically remember
tracking my calories

00:47:21.890 --> 00:47:26.060 align:middle line:84%
and burning approximately 1,800
a day and consuming only 1,400.

00:47:26.060 --> 00:47:29.052 align:middle line:84%
And if every day came where
those numbers were reversed,

00:47:29.052 --> 00:47:30.510 align:middle line:84%
I would get so
depressed and angry.

00:47:30.510 --> 00:47:31.430 align:middle line:90%
It was unbelievable.

00:47:31.430 --> 00:47:33.650 align:middle line:84%
And I had to super
compensate the next day

00:47:33.650 --> 00:47:36.092 align:middle line:84%
to make sure that I was burning
more than I was consuming.

00:47:36.092 --> 00:47:37.550 align:middle line:84%
One of the things
that happens when

00:47:37.550 --> 00:47:39.440 align:middle line:84%
you have an eating
disorder is you

00:47:39.440 --> 00:47:41.540 align:middle line:84%
go into this specific
type of depression

00:47:41.540 --> 00:47:44.528 align:middle line:84%
where you just don't find
pleasure out of things anymore.

00:47:44.528 --> 00:47:45.328 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:47:45.328 --> 00:48:07.800 align:middle line:10%
(SINGING)

00:48:07.800 --> 00:48:10.180 align:middle line:10%
The only thing that I
really found pleasure out of

00:48:10.180 --> 00:48:15.220 align:middle line:10%
was exercising in huge amounts
and working out really hard

00:48:15.220 --> 00:48:18.040 align:middle line:10%
and restricting my calories and
seeing how far I can actually

00:48:18.040 --> 00:48:18.970 align:middle line:10%
push it or stretch it.

00:48:18.970 --> 00:48:21.640 align:middle line:84%
My emotions were
all over the place.

00:48:21.640 --> 00:48:24.820 align:middle line:84%
To say life became a struggle
is putting it lightly.

00:48:24.820 --> 00:48:28.360 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't go as far as
saying that I was suicidal,

00:48:28.360 --> 00:48:31.085 align:middle line:84%
but I definitely had
given up on life.

00:48:31.085 --> 00:48:32.710 align:middle line:84%
And I did not want
to live another day.

00:48:32.710 --> 00:48:37.750 align:middle line:90%


00:48:37.750 --> 00:48:40.360 align:middle line:84%
I literally would pray
that I would go over

00:48:40.360 --> 00:48:43.000 align:middle line:84%
to the streets of Manhattan
in the afternoon to work

00:48:43.000 --> 00:48:45.580 align:middle line:84%
and I would get hit by a
bus going out of control

00:48:45.580 --> 00:48:48.910 align:middle line:84%
or get killed in gang warfare
or get shot or stabbed to death.

00:48:48.910 --> 00:48:51.943 align:middle line:84%
I would have to say
my lowest point was

00:48:51.943 --> 00:48:53.860 align:middle line:84%
when I was contemplating
jumping into the East

00:48:53.860 --> 00:48:55.188 align:middle line:90%
River in Manhattan.

00:48:55.188 --> 00:48:58.540 align:middle line:90%


00:48:58.540 --> 00:49:01.250 align:middle line:84%
At that moment, I
just started thinking

00:49:01.250 --> 00:49:07.160 align:middle line:84%
about my mom who is back
home, living by herself,

00:49:07.160 --> 00:49:10.400 align:middle line:90%
and a lot of my close friends.

00:49:10.400 --> 00:49:14.330 align:middle line:84%
And I was wondering, if
they even would care,

00:49:14.330 --> 00:49:16.790 align:middle line:90%
because I didn't.

00:49:16.790 --> 00:49:19.190 align:middle line:90%
And then my phone rang.

00:49:19.190 --> 00:49:21.390 align:middle line:84%
At the very moment, I
stepped onto that rung.

00:49:21.390 --> 00:49:24.903 align:middle line:84%
And it was my friend Jessica
back home in Pennsylvania.

00:49:24.903 --> 00:49:26.820 align:middle line:84%
And it's ironic how
timing works in this life,

00:49:26.820 --> 00:49:28.970 align:middle line:84%
but it couldn't have
come at a better

00:49:28.970 --> 00:49:31.010 align:middle line:84%
time, because she
basically talked me

00:49:31.010 --> 00:49:32.570 align:middle line:90%
down off of that handrail.

00:49:32.570 --> 00:49:34.640 align:middle line:90%
And I went sat down on a bench.

00:49:34.640 --> 00:49:38.900 align:middle line:84%
The root problem was I
was so mineral deficient.

00:49:38.900 --> 00:49:40.850 align:middle line:84%
And I had such lack
of food in my system

00:49:40.850 --> 00:49:43.070 align:middle line:84%
that I just wasn't
thinking properly.

00:49:43.070 --> 00:49:46.100 align:middle line:84%
It never really was
about the food per say.

00:49:46.100 --> 00:49:51.140 align:middle line:84%
It was more about my interaction
and relationships with people.

00:49:51.140 --> 00:49:52.970 align:middle line:90%
Good relationships were fine.

00:49:52.970 --> 00:49:55.400 align:middle line:84%
Ones that were a little
rocky just kind of like

00:49:55.400 --> 00:49:57.240 align:middle line:90%
triggered me like that.

00:49:57.240 --> 00:50:00.410 align:middle line:84%
And I would basically
take everything out

00:50:00.410 --> 00:50:03.230 align:middle line:90%
on food and fitness.

00:50:03.230 --> 00:50:06.960 align:middle line:84%
When I began this journey back
to normalcy, it was not easy.

00:50:06.960 --> 00:50:08.300 align:middle line:90%
It was not an easy road.

00:50:08.300 --> 00:50:10.160 align:middle line:84%
I had to accept
the fact that I was

00:50:10.160 --> 00:50:11.510 align:middle line:90%
going to gain some weight back.

00:50:11.510 --> 00:50:13.550 align:middle line:90%
I was 145 pounds.

00:50:13.550 --> 00:50:15.050 align:middle line:90%
I was 6 foot 3.

00:50:15.050 --> 00:50:17.170 align:middle line:84%
And I was totally
zeroing in on 140.

00:50:17.170 --> 00:50:18.170 align:middle line:90%
And that's how I worked.

00:50:18.170 --> 00:50:20.330 align:middle line:84%
