01:21:13.030 --> 01:21:15.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Every thing in the body
has multiple functions,

01:21:15.620 --> 01:21:17.280 align:middle line:90%
multiple sites of action.

01:21:17.280 --> 01:21:20.630 align:middle line:84%
So when you give a drug that
you think is working one site,

01:21:20.630 --> 01:21:23.480 align:middle line:84%
it's working and doing things
all over the body in ways

01:21:23.480 --> 01:21:25.700 align:middle line:90%
that we may not even comprehend.

01:21:25.700 --> 01:21:27.680 align:middle line:10%
That's why when you
look at pharmaceuticals,

01:21:27.680 --> 01:21:29.360 align:middle line:10%
the list of side
effects are huge,

01:21:29.360 --> 01:21:30.717 align:middle line:10%
and often including death.

01:21:30.717 --> 01:21:33.050 align:middle line:10%
If you've watched television
and you see the commercials

01:21:33.050 --> 01:21:35.780 align:middle line:10%
for many of the
pharmaceuticals, they actually

01:21:35.780 --> 01:21:37.310 align:middle line:10%
show people having
a wonderful time.

01:21:37.310 --> 01:21:40.310 align:middle line:10%
And then they say and, by the
way, this drug may kill you.

01:21:40.310 --> 01:21:42.680 align:middle line:10%
That is one thing
that does not happen

01:21:42.680 --> 01:21:45.770 align:middle line:10%
when you eat the right
foods, when you exercise,

01:21:45.770 --> 01:21:47.970 align:middle line:10%
when you incorporate
periodic fasting.

01:21:47.970 --> 01:21:49.970 align:middle line:10%
>> So what we found was
that high blood pressure

01:21:49.970 --> 01:21:52.110 align:middle line:10%
medications,
cholesterol medications,

01:21:52.110 --> 01:21:56.180 align:middle line:10%
these are common things taken by
many, many different Americans,

01:21:56.180 --> 01:22:01.650 align:middle line:10%
but they hurt their stem cells
ability to grow and culture.

01:22:01.650 --> 01:22:04.370 align:middle line:84%
So that's not a good thing
if you think about the fact

01:22:04.370 --> 01:22:08.660 align:middle line:84%
that these medications are
impacting your body's own stem

01:22:08.660 --> 01:22:13.430 align:middle line:84%
cells and their ability to
maintain and repair that body.

01:22:13.430 --> 01:22:15.180 align:middle line:90%
That's a big problem.

01:22:15.180 --> 01:22:17.660 align:middle line:84%
So as an example, we've
treated lots of patients

01:22:17.660 --> 01:22:21.530 align:middle line:84%
through the years with
tendinopathy due to taking

01:22:21.530 --> 01:22:23.510 align:middle line:90%
a specific type of antibiotic.

01:22:23.510 --> 01:22:25.850 align:middle line:84%
>> I literally
became debilitated.

01:22:25.850 --> 01:22:29.570 align:middle line:84%
I had shoulder pain,
neck pain, leg pain.

01:22:29.570 --> 01:22:31.020 align:middle line:90%
I could barely walk.

01:22:31.020 --> 01:22:32.660 align:middle line:84%
I even had a hard
time breathing.

01:22:32.660 --> 01:22:37.070 align:middle line:84%
Two of my discs had completely
herniated into my spine.

01:22:37.070 --> 01:22:39.175 align:middle line:90%
I really felt I was dying.

01:22:39.175 --> 01:22:40.550 align:middle line:84%
>> It was a known
problem though.

01:22:40.550 --> 01:22:42.300 align:middle line:84%
They'll take this
antibiotic, because they

01:22:42.300 --> 01:22:43.280 align:middle line:90%
have a common cold.

01:22:43.280 --> 01:22:45.657 align:middle line:84%
And the next thing they
know, they're in chronic pain

01:22:45.657 --> 01:22:46.490 align:middle line:90%
all over their body.

01:22:46.490 --> 01:22:47.480 align:middle line:90%
Why?

01:22:47.480 --> 01:22:49.670 align:middle line:84%
Because that
particular antibiotic

01:22:49.670 --> 01:22:53.270 align:middle line:84%
reduces the stem cells
ability in their body

01:22:53.270 --> 01:22:55.130 align:middle line:90%
to repair their tendons.

01:22:55.130 --> 01:22:57.500 align:middle line:84%
And we all get tendon
wear and tear every day

01:22:57.500 --> 01:22:59.000 align:middle line:90%
that needs to be repaired.

01:22:59.000 --> 01:23:00.740 align:middle line:84%
So one of the things
we started realizing

01:23:00.740 --> 01:23:04.340 align:middle line:84%
is that when we were going to
use the patient's own cells

01:23:04.340 --> 01:23:06.470 align:middle line:84%
to try to repair
something, we had

01:23:06.470 --> 01:23:08.360 align:middle line:84%
to have patients clean
up their lifestyle,

01:23:08.360 --> 01:23:09.740 align:middle line:90%
including their diet.

01:23:09.740 --> 01:23:12.260 align:middle line:84%
We make sure that they're
fasting when they come in,

01:23:12.260 --> 01:23:16.130 align:middle line:84%
because we know that fasting
can increase the body's ability

01:23:16.130 --> 01:23:17.930 align:middle line:90%
to help prepare itself.

01:23:17.930 --> 01:23:20.870 align:middle line:84%
>> For the next several weeks,
after each time I do a fasting

01:23:20.870 --> 01:23:25.100 align:middle line:84%
mimicking diet, I end up with
a significantly reduced pain

01:23:25.100 --> 01:23:26.510 align:middle line:90%
in all my joints.

01:23:26.510 --> 01:23:29.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Polycystic ovary syndrome,
that's one of my niches.

01:23:29.840 --> 01:23:31.290 align:middle line:90%
I deal a lot with hormones.

01:23:31.290 --> 01:23:33.170 align:middle line:84%
If you take an
unhealthy woman and you

01:23:33.170 --> 01:23:35.240 align:middle line:84%
trick her body into
getting pregnant,

01:23:35.240 --> 01:23:36.720 align:middle line:90%
often it will be rejected.

01:23:36.720 --> 01:23:39.680 align:middle line:84%
And if it's successful, it's
not usually very successful,

01:23:39.680 --> 01:23:42.800 align:middle line:84%
because you often will have
very severe complications later

01:23:42.800 --> 01:23:45.410 align:middle line:84%
on towards the end of
pregnancy, like high blood

01:23:45.410 --> 01:23:49.040 align:middle line:84%
pressure, toxemia, preterm
labor, a lot of diabetes,

01:23:49.040 --> 01:23:51.200 align:middle line:84%
many, many complications
in these women

01:23:51.200 --> 01:23:53.000 align:middle line:84%
when they do not
get them healthy,

01:23:53.000 --> 01:23:54.900 align:middle line:84%
but trick them into
getting pregnant.

01:23:54.900 --> 01:23:58.380 align:middle line:84%
So then she came to
me and she just said,

01:23:58.380 --> 01:24:00.110 align:middle line:84%
I've tried the
conventional route.

01:24:00.110 --> 01:24:03.110 align:middle line:84%
I've spent thousands of
dollars trying to get pregnant.

01:24:03.110 --> 01:24:07.760 align:middle line:84%
And, well, I've heard that there
is this integrative approach.

01:24:07.760 --> 01:24:09.290 align:middle line:90%
So what can you do to help me?

01:24:09.290 --> 01:24:11.240 align:middle line:90%
She did everything I asked.

01:24:11.240 --> 01:24:13.280 align:middle line:90%
So she had a large breakfast.

01:24:13.280 --> 01:24:14.880 align:middle line:90%
She had a medium lunch.

01:24:14.880 --> 01:24:16.160 align:middle line:90%
She had a tiny dinner.

01:24:16.160 --> 01:24:18.170 align:middle line:90%
She didn't eat after 7:00 PM.

01:24:18.170 --> 01:24:19.550 align:middle line:90%
She began exercising.

01:24:19.550 --> 01:24:22.250 align:middle line:90%
She ate no processed foods.

01:24:22.250 --> 01:24:23.900 align:middle line:90%
She did everything right.

01:24:23.900 --> 01:24:27.410 align:middle line:84%
Then after a month,
I put her on Prolon.

01:24:27.410 --> 01:24:31.070 align:middle line:84%
After three cycles,
she got pregnant.

01:24:31.070 --> 01:24:34.220 align:middle line:90%
That was almost a year ago.

01:24:34.220 --> 01:24:36.530 align:middle line:84%
And she has recently
delivered her baby.

01:24:36.530 --> 01:24:39.340 align:middle line:10%
She is a beautiful healthy baby.

01:24:39.340 --> 01:24:41.210 align:middle line:90%
She is in her late 30s now.

01:24:41.210 --> 01:24:43.010 align:middle line:84%
She's been trying
for all these years.

01:24:43.010 --> 01:24:44.870 align:middle line:84%
>> Depending on the
therapeutic use,

01:24:44.870 --> 01:24:47.580 align:middle line:84%
you have to really
understand this and use it

01:24:47.580 --> 01:24:48.380 align:middle line:90%
to your advantage.

01:24:48.380 --> 01:24:52.020 align:middle line:84%
So for example, when we do
it for metabolic syndrome,

01:24:52.020 --> 01:24:55.580 align:middle line:84%
diabetes, and cancer, we
do between four and five

01:24:55.580 --> 01:24:59.330 align:middle line:84%
