with various therapies.

01:24:59.330 --> 01:25:00.440 align:middle line:90%
That's sufficient.

01:25:00.440 --> 01:25:04.700 align:middle line:84%
When we look at autoimmunities,
instead we go to seven days.

01:25:04.700 --> 01:25:05.670 align:middle line:90%
Why do we do that?

01:25:05.670 --> 01:25:09.230 align:middle line:84%
Because we now want
to do more destruction

01:25:09.230 --> 01:25:12.470 align:middle line:84%
of damaged cells, the
autoimmune cells, in this case.

01:25:12.470 --> 01:25:14.480 align:middle line:84%
So if you do a
shorter fast, you're

01:25:14.480 --> 01:25:16.940 align:middle line:84%
not really going to benefit
that much, because you

01:25:16.940 --> 01:25:22.370 align:middle line:84%
don't have enough time to
destroy the damaged cells.

01:25:22.370 --> 01:25:25.760 align:middle line:84%
And also, you have
less rebuilding

01:25:25.760 --> 01:25:27.380 align:middle line:90%
using the stem cells.

01:25:27.380 --> 01:25:30.320 align:middle line:84%
So this is why it's so important
to understand the mechanisms

01:25:30.320 --> 01:25:33.950 align:middle line:84%
behind it and for each
purpose really using

01:25:33.950 --> 01:25:37.310 align:middle line:84%
a different fasting-based
intervention.

01:25:37.310 --> 01:25:39.410 align:middle line:84%
>> I was working on a
documentary for the BBC,

01:25:39.410 --> 01:25:41.360 align:middle line:84%
